Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as the exclusive sales agent are pleased to present to market 7-9 Countess Street, Mosman. Designed by renowned architecture firm, Innovate Architects, 7-9 Countess Street, Mosman is a DA approved North facing luxury boutique development site. The development consists of large well-designed apartments with flowing, open-plan floor plans oriented to take advantage of natural light and outlook that appeals to the area’s affluent downsizers. Situated over two levels, the top floor apartments enjoy large sun-drenched terraces, whilst the ground floor apartments benefit from patio areas and large private lawns. Cleverly designed with one level of basement parking, reducing build costs, accommodating 13 car spaces across 6 lock up garages and 2 visitor parking spaces. 
A lift provides access from the car park to the 2 floors of apartments above.

The prestigious nature of the suburb is reflected in its affluent demographic and is one of the driving factors behind the area’s strong property market. Lifestyle focussed location only a short walk to shops, cafes, restaurants, and public transport to Sydney CBD. Only moments from the crystal water and white sandy beach of Balmoral, parks, prestigious schools, Taronga Zoo, and scenic walks around Middle Head all within 5.5km* of Sydney CBD.

7-9 Countess Street, Mosman benefits from the following key attributes:

•DA approval for 4 x 3 Bedroom & 2 x 2 bedroom apartments with 13 basement car spaces (6 LUG)
•Well-designed open-plan floor plan apartments
•Designed to take advantage of natural light and outlook
•Top floor apartments enjoy large sun-drenched terraces
•Ground floor apartments capitalise on large patio areas and private lawns
•Lift providing access from the basement carpark to the building’s two floors 
•Large total site area of 1032.2sqm*
•Approved GFA: 678.08sqm
•Approved NSA: 633.60sqm
•Max Potential GFA: 722.54sqm*


7-9 Countess Street, Mosman will be sold via Private Treaty with a price of $9,000,000.

Inspections to be held by appointment as per COVID-19 Greater Sydney restriction requirements. Please enquire directly with the exclusive agents to arrange a private viewing.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approx.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent is pleased to present to the market 742 Military Road, Mosman, a premium retail freehold investment with significant development upside (STCA). The three-storey property, with a captivating art deco facade, has significant curb appeal with just under 17m* of frontage to both Military Road and Melaleuca Lane, and boasting a rear loading dock with parking. Anchored by Country Road, owned by an international publicly listed company with a net annual income of $504,457*. 

The property also presents a significant future development opportunity for a shop top housing development (STCA). The prestigious nature of the suburb is reflected in its affluent demographic and is one of the driving factors behind the area’s strong property market. The subject property holds a high exposure location along Mosman’s busiest street (Military Road) and is surrounded by an array of high-end retailers and popular eateries.

742 Military Road, Mosman benefits from the following details:
 
•Premium retail freehold investment with development upside (STCA)
•Anchored by Country Road, owned by an international publicly listed company with a net annual income of $504,457*
•Floor Area: 1,151sqm*
•Generous site area of 679sqm*
•Favourable B2 local centre zoning permitting a shop top housing development (STCA)
•FSR: 2.5:1
•Height Limit: 15m 
•High exposure location along Mosman’s busiest street, Military Road 
•Frontage of 17m* to Military Road and 17m* to Melaleuca Lane 
•Premium location in the heart of Mosman Villages retail precinct amongst other premium brands, cafes, and restaurants, only 5.5km* from Sydney CBD

742 Military Road, Mosman will be sold via an online Public Auction at auctionWORKS on Tuesday 17 August 2021 at 10:30am (registration, livestream & online bidding will be available)

Inspections to be held by appointment as per COVID-19 Greater Sydney restriction requirements. Please enquire directly with the exclusive agents to arrange a private viewing.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Prime Position in the heart of Mosman

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive selling agent, on behalf of the Department of Planning, Industry and Environment, is pleased to present a fantastic mixed-use development opportunity in the heart of one of Sydney’s most affluent and desirable suburbs: 7 – 11 Spit Road, Mosman.

This raw 1,424sqm* development site allows purchasers to acquire a B2 – Local Centre zoned block that commands a prominent corner position in Mosman. The B-Line bus stop, which provides frequent rapid bus services to Sydney CBD and the Northern Beaches, sits on its doorstep, with various retail shops, restaurants, supermarkets and cafes just a short walk away. With demolition complete, the site presents an exciting opportunity for a high-end shop top development (STCA) on a level block with two large frontages to both Spit Road and Clifford Street providing great access for construction.

7 – 11 Spit Road, Mosman benefits from the following key attributes:
 • Sizeable site area of 1,424sqm*
 • B2 – Local Centre Zoning permitting with consent shop top 
    housing
 • 3:1 FSR and 15m Height Limit
 • Desirable Location – proximity to a multitude of shops, 
    eateries, attractions, beaches and more
 • Large dual frontages to Spit Road and Clifford Street
 • Building demolition complete
 • Level Site with great access for construction
 • Potential GFA of 4,272sqm*

DPIE is seeking Expressions of Interest in relation to the property closing Friday 30th of April at 3:00pm. Successful proponents will be invited to participate in the Select Tender Process.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

Note: All figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.
